	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm pretty sure most modern notebook computers have voltage regulators inside, which means any PSU around 20VDC should work fine.<br />I've tested this on my older Dell which needed 20VDC. I used 2 12V lead acid batteries in series and it worked fine.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


