		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The laptops I had this happen with were HP Pavilion ZT3000 with Mobility Radeon 9200 graphics from about 2004 (before RoHS). They had a host of issues, including that the power regulation and cooling for the GPU was inadequate, but they started failing en masse after about two weeks after we issued universal car/air AC adapters for them. HP denied warranty claims, citing overvoltage as the issue.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
